olive oil
1 onion
1 capsicum
2 clove garlic
1 packet Mild Chorizo
1 sachet Berbere seasoning
1 tin chopped tomatoes
1 tsp brown sugar
¼ cup water
2 eggs
1 packet sourdough bread
1 bag salad leaves
1 drizzle white wine vinegar
1 block Greek salad cheese/feta cheese

Thinly slice the brown onion. Roughly chop the
capsicum. Finely chop the garlic. Cut the mild
chorizo into thin half-moons.

In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over
a medium-high heat. Cook the chorizo, tossing,
until golden, 4-5 minutes. Transfer to a plate.

Return the frying pan to a medium-high heat. Add
a drizzle of olive oil, if needed. Cook the onion
and capsicum until softened, 4-5 minutes. Add
the Berbere seasoning and garlic and cook until
fragrant, 1 minute. Add the chopped tomatoes,
brown sugar and the water. Reduce heat and
simmer until thickened, 3-4 minutes. Return the
cooked chorizo to the pan and stir. Season with
salt and pepper.

Using a spoon, make two small wells in the sauce.
Crack one egg into each well. Cover the pan with
a lid or foil and cook until the egg whites have set,
3-5 minutes. Remove from the heat.

TIP: To avoid getting shells in your sauce, crack
each egg into a mug or small bowl individually,
then gently pour into the wells.

While the sauce is cooking, thickly slice the
sourdough loaf. Toast or grill to your liking.
When the bread is toasted, drizzle with olive oil.
In a medium bowl, add the rocket with a drizzle
of white wine vinegar and olive oil and toss to
combine. Season to taste.

Divide the shakshuka and sourdough between
plates. Crumble with the cheese and top with the
rocket salad to serve.